03:10.374 --> 03:12.476
He's what we call a hard target.

03:12.509 --> 03:14.244
You know, mean he, uh...
he sleeps light,

03:14.277 --> 03:15.646
you know, with one eye open.

03:15.679 --> 03:18.081
You ain't gonna ever really
get the...

03:18.114 --> 03:19.282
get the drop on him.

03:21.685 --> 03:22.986
So, what's next?

03:23.019 --> 03:24.988
Well, I follow him.

03:25.021 --> 03:26.923
You know, bring you back
some useful intel--

03:26.957 --> 03:29.526
you know, where he lives,
you know, if he has a family,

03:29.560 --> 03:31.862
try to find his soft spots.

03:31.895 --> 03:33.864
And say you get yourself caught.

03:33.897 --> 03:35.432
(dog barking in distance)

03:35.466 --> 03:37.868
How's Reed gonna take it
we trying to follow him?

03:37.901 --> 03:39.970
TOP NOTCH:
You ain't got to worry about me.

03:40.003 --> 03:42.172
They don't call the man
Top Notch for nothing.

03:44.007 --> 03:46.543
I know it's scary,
but we need to push forward,

03:46.577 --> 03:49.279
build up leverage,
a protection plan.

03:49.312 --> 03:51.715
Protection plan, and that's it?

03:51.748 --> 03:53.350
That's the only option?

03:53.384 --> 03:57.287
No, there's one
other thing you can do:

03:57.320 --> 03:58.489
run.

03:59.556 --> 04:01.492
Cuba's your best bet these days,

04:01.525 --> 04:04.495
but, you know,

04:04.528 --> 04:08.499
once the CIA got you
in their crosshairs...

04:08.532 --> 04:10.634
Yeah?

04:10.667 --> 04:13.169
...there ain't no real cover.

04:15.071 --> 04:17.273
(helicopter whirring
in distance)

04:21.378 --> 04:23.547
(distant chatter)

04:25.549 --> 04:27.551
(keys jingling)

04:32.188 --> 04:34.190
She gone again?

04:43.934 --> 04:46.036
(lock clicks, car door opens)

04:46.069 --> 04:48.071
I'll put the word out.

04:52.275 --> 04:54.277
(car door shuts, engine starts)

05:02.753 --> 05:05.288
There's got to be a better way.

05:05.321 --> 05:07.323
There ain't.

05:27.410 --> 05:29.913
Teddy?

05:29.946 --> 05:32.082
I've been trying
to give you space, but...

05:32.115 --> 05:34.317
it's been weeks.

05:36.252 --> 05:40.390
Yeah, I can't abandon this,
you know.

05:40.423 --> 05:42.292
Not now.

05:42.325 --> 05:44.628
Besides, it's not so bad, right?

05:44.661 --> 05:48.398
Sun, surf, fighting the commies?

05:48.431 --> 05:50.634
We can fight communism
somewhere else.

05:50.667 --> 05:53.003
If Nicaragua falls,
Honduras and Guatemala are next.

05:53.036 --> 05:54.471
I'm not letting that happen.

05:54.505 --> 05:56.673
In a year, I can leave.

05:56.707 --> 05:58.709
Just give me a year.

06:00.811 --> 06:03.146
You know, hedgehogs, in winter,
when it's freezing,

06:03.179 --> 06:05.782
they huddle together
to keep warm.

06:05.816 --> 06:07.951
But then their sharp spines
prick each other,

06:07.984 --> 06:09.586
so they move apart.

06:09.620 --> 06:12.756
But then they get cold,
so they huddle together again,

06:12.789 --> 06:15.325
prick each other again,
over and over.

06:15.358 --> 06:17.327
(zipper zipping)

06:17.360 --> 06:18.962
Okay.

06:21.197 --> 06:23.800
So we're hedgehogs.
(chuckles softly)

06:23.834 --> 06:26.803
Can't be together,
can't be apart.

06:27.871 --> 06:29.339
I'm saying it feels like

06:29.372 --> 06:31.074
we've had this
conversation before.

06:42.753 --> 06:45.388
You can finish this
without me, yeah?

06:57.568 --> 07:00.236
Yeah, she'll come home
for a day or two,

07:00.270 --> 07:02.673
-say all the right things...
-(TV playing indistinctly)

07:02.706 --> 07:04.207
(sighs)

07:04.240 --> 07:07.310
Then she'll be gone again.

07:07.343 --> 07:09.680
I, uh...

07:09.713 --> 07:12.482
I can't take her to school,
not like this.

07:12.515 --> 07:14.651
-(indistinct chatter
over phone)
-(sighs)

07:14.685 --> 07:17.153
No telling what she'd do
if she was alone.

07:17.187 --> 07:19.890
WOMAN (over phone):
Why don't you both come?

07:19.923 --> 07:22.258
To Texas?

07:22.292 --> 07:24.327
Take a break from the city.

07:24.360 --> 07:26.096
Bring her to a new environment.

07:26.129 --> 07:28.331
-Hmm.
-Give her a clean slate.

07:28.364 --> 07:30.867
Well, no, I never really
thought of that before.

07:30.901 --> 07:32.836
(indistinct chatter over phone)

07:32.869 --> 07:34.938
You sure it wouldn't be
putting you out?

07:34.971 --> 07:36.973
(indistinct chatter over phone)

07:40.811 --> 07:43.546
Well, I am still suspended
from my job, so...

07:43.580 --> 07:46.883
(knocking on door)

07:46.917 --> 07:50.520
I'll have to think about it.
Hey, let me, uh, call you back.

07:50.553 --> 07:51.788
(indistinct chatter over phone)

07:51.822 --> 07:53.924
All right, love you, sis.

08:01.598 --> 08:04.100
-Andre Wright?
-Yeah?

08:04.134 --> 08:06.236
My name's Kate Miller.

08:06.269 --> 08:08.538
Do you have a few minutes?

08:08.571 --> 08:10.540
Few minutes for what?

08:10.573 --> 08:12.375
I believe we can
help each other.

08:12.408 --> 08:14.978
My agency's knee-deep
in a highly sensitive op,

08:15.011 --> 08:18.381
and I came across your name
during prep.

08:18.414 --> 08:20.216
I'm sorry, what agency?

08:20.250 --> 08:21.885
And how did you get my address?

08:21.918 --> 08:23.453
Detective Han gave it to me.

08:23.486 --> 08:25.221
(whispers):
Detective Han...

08:25.255 --> 08:30.093
He's the LAPD'S liaison
to the FBI, DEA, CIA.

08:30.126 --> 08:33.563
We're running at
a Colombian drug cartel.

08:33.596 --> 08:35.565
But you know what it's like
working for

08:35.598 --> 08:37.400
a government bureaucracy.

08:37.433 --> 08:40.837
Higher-ups only want to go after
the head honchos.

08:40.871 --> 08:43.239
Makes for a better
news conference.

08:43.273 --> 08:46.409
But it's the smaller guys
that need to be taken down.

08:46.442 --> 08:48.845
Look, you know, I appreciate you
coming all this way,

08:48.879 --> 08:50.781
but... got a lot of shit
going on, so...

08:50.814 --> 08:52.482
The ones doing damage
right here,

08:52.515 --> 08:56.386
in our neighborhoods--
dealers like Franklin Saint.

08:58.822 --> 09:00.924
Did you just say Franklin Saint?

09:00.957 --> 09:03.694
A witness recanted,

09:03.727 --> 09:06.129
Saint's file was sealed,

09:06.162 --> 09:09.866
and your job was made
all but impossible.

09:09.900 --> 09:12.635
I'm here to level
the playing field.

09:14.871 --> 09:16.172
(smoke alarm beeping)

09:16.206 --> 09:19.009
Oh, shit! Oh, shit!

09:19.042 --> 09:20.610
Shit. Fuck!

09:20.643 --> 09:22.145
Shit. God...

09:22.178 --> 09:24.214
Come on. (groans)

09:25.548 --> 09:27.550
(groaning)

09:27.583 --> 09:29.519
God, come on, man.

09:32.923 --> 09:35.525
We're on the same side,
Officer Wright.

09:37.861 --> 09:40.563
(dog barking in distance)

09:45.101 --> 09:46.937
(door closes)

10:13.296 --> 10:15.298
That's it.

10:18.301 --> 10:19.535
Whoa.

10:19.569 --> 10:21.371
Hold up. (chuckles)

10:21.404 --> 10:23.206
Your keys.

10:25.575 --> 10:26.743
Fuck.

10:27.744 --> 10:30.280
-You all right?
-(sighs)

10:36.719 --> 10:40.123
You have a girlfriend, Franklin?

10:41.257 --> 10:43.159
A girlfriend or...?

10:46.129 --> 10:48.098
Nah.

10:48.131 --> 10:50.901
Nothing steady.

10:50.934 --> 10:53.636
You ever been in love?

10:56.773 --> 10:58.308
(chuckles)

10:58.341 --> 11:02.278
You not about to profess
or nothing, right? (laughs)

11:02.312 --> 11:05.715
I think I was once.
I don't know.

11:05.748 --> 11:07.717
You don't know
if you were in love or...?

11:07.750 --> 11:09.719
I mean, I-I cared about her,

11:09.752 --> 11:11.955
thought I could see myself
with her,

11:11.988 --> 11:14.724
but we were young, changing.

11:14.757 --> 11:18.094
Maybe what I thought was right
weren't the thing after all.

11:18.128 --> 11:21.464
Oh, yeah.

11:21.497 --> 11:23.433
See, that's-that's
exactly it, man.

11:23.466 --> 11:25.802
That is just right.
You got to wait...

11:25.836 --> 11:28.905
long as you can so that there is
as little chance as possible

11:28.939 --> 11:31.441
