38:53.482 --> 38:56.217
A'ight, run home to your daddy.

38:56.250 --> 38:58.319
Stuck-up bitch!

39:08.830 --> 39:11.032
(grunts softly)

39:23.444 --> 39:25.680
(crying)

39:27.448 --> 39:29.618
(sniffles)

39:29.651 --> 39:32.153
(window slides open)

39:32.186 --> 39:34.656
(footsteps)

39:34.689 --> 39:37.926
Mel?

39:37.959 --> 39:40.094
Mel, is that you?
(chuckles)

39:40.128 --> 39:42.497
Hey, baby,
I just realized that...

39:42.531 --> 39:44.533
*

39:51.906 --> 39:54.943
How'd you get in here?

39:54.976 --> 39:58.713
Same way I have
since I was eight years old.

39:58.747 --> 40:00.348
That my gun?

40:00.381 --> 40:03.918
You went looking for it
in the wrong place.

40:05.486 --> 40:07.522
Put it down, Franklin.

40:16.064 --> 40:18.032
(sighs)

40:18.066 --> 40:20.869
I don't suppose, if I asked you
if you told anybody

40:20.902 --> 40:24.072
about this shit,
you'd tell me the truth?

40:24.105 --> 40:26.875
Do you know who
these people are, Franklin?

40:26.908 --> 40:29.243
-What they're involved in?
-Sit down.

40:41.055 --> 40:42.691
Put it in the folder.

40:46.527 --> 40:49.898
Look, you're angry and afraid.
I get it.

40:49.931 --> 40:52.100
But you don't have to do this.

40:52.133 --> 40:54.202
Put down the gun down,
and we can talk.

40:54.235 --> 40:57.538
Ain't nothing you can tell me
I don't already know, Andre.

40:57.572 --> 40:59.941
I know I helped raise you.

40:59.974 --> 41:04.045
You were a good kid, one of
the smartest kids I ever knew.

41:06.080 --> 41:09.050
You're not gonna kill a cop
in his own house.

41:24.966 --> 41:28.102
You took me to that crack den,

41:28.136 --> 41:31.405
gave me a chance,
so now I'm-a give you one.

41:31.439 --> 41:34.208
Forget you ever saw
any of this shit, Andre.

41:34.242 --> 41:38.579
Get out of town with Mel,
and don't ever come back.

41:38.613 --> 41:40.815
Who is this man
that you're protecting?

41:40.849 --> 41:42.951
Huh? You know he don't give
two shits about you.

41:42.984 --> 41:45.586
Leave L.A. forever, Andre.
Disappear.

41:45.620 --> 41:49.457
And just maybe the two of us
can make it out this shit alive.

41:57.498 --> 41:58.900
(laughs softly)

41:58.933 --> 42:01.102
Okay, Franklin.

42:01.135 --> 42:04.238
I'll leave now, tonight.

42:04.272 --> 42:06.440
I'll get Mel far away from you,

42:06.474 --> 42:09.177
get her cleaned up
and in school.

42:11.212 --> 42:13.214
But then I'm coming back.

42:14.716 --> 42:17.451
I've put in 18 years
out of my 20,

42:17.485 --> 42:19.520
and I'm not gonna let you
run me away

42:19.553 --> 42:21.589
and destroy this community.

42:21.622 --> 42:25.426
So, you want to play
cops and robbers?

42:25.459 --> 42:27.662
Okay, we can do that.

42:30.198 --> 42:33.668
I'll come back, fresh start,

42:33.702 --> 42:36.537
and it's you and me,
head-to-head.

42:37.739 --> 42:39.808
And we'll see who's standing.

42:39.841 --> 42:42.176
Here's your file.

42:42.210 --> 42:44.178
You ain't a fucking killer.

42:44.212 --> 42:46.881
Now, get the fuck
out of my house.

42:54.055 --> 42:56.224
You're right, Andre.

42:59.660 --> 43:01.495
I'm not a killer.

43:15.209 --> 43:18.412
(shuddering breaths)

43:21.515 --> 43:23.251
(groans quietly)

43:27.722 --> 43:29.924
(dog barking in distance)

43:50.945 --> 43:52.947
*

45:42.490 --> 45:44.392
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

45:46.660 --> 45:48.329
Never get too greedy, Franklin.

45:48.362 --> 45:50.999
The minute you do that,
you lost your advantage.

45:55.069 --> 45:58.372
From here on out,
we'll only deal
with high-level customers.

45:59.908 --> 46:02.376
-You having trust issues?
-No way.

46:04.612 --> 46:07.581
It's up to you
to protect everyone.
Can you do it or not?

46:09.884 --> 46:11.785
How are you sleeping at night?

46:11.886 --> 46:13.187
Like a baby.
